parameters: \nc<>It has been three years since Cashew Nut's invitation.

\nc<>As someone who had just entered middle school, I devoted
myself even more to the activities of being a magical girl.

\nc<>Due to sudden changes in the environment, I found myself
preferring familiar things and falling into the illusion
that I, as a second-year middle school student, was special.

\nc<>It's possible that it was natural for my friends to drift
away from me, as I became obsessed with those 'unspeakable
things'.
\nc<>I don't really think anyone is to blame.

\nc<>I wanted to help the citizens. They wanted friends they
could spend time with.
\nc<>Our hopes didn't align, that's all there is to it.

\nc<>But then, I wonder when I will find friends who can
understand me.

\nc<>I wonder if there is anyone who would be a good match for
me, a magical girl, to begin with.

\nc<>When I think about it, my chest becomes so tight that it's
hard to breathe.
\nc<>Before I knew it, I had stopped reaching out to others.

\nc<>...I've already arrived. I wonder why time flies by so
quickly when I think about pointless things.

\nc<>Reina doesn't seem to be here yet. Maybe I'll kill some time
by doing a random search... Huh?

\nc<>It's bad, Levantia! The succubi have started causing a
ruckus near the outskirts!

\nc<>Candy and Sherbet are also on their way, but they might be
late because class is still in session, meow!
\nc<>I'm coming to the outskirts right away, meow!

\nc<>No, it's not good. If I go now, I'll be significantly late
for the promise.

\nc<>(Didn't Reina say it? That there's something important to
talk about.) (Are the others more important and friends
don't matter!?)

\nc<>(Even if Candy and Sherbet can't make it... If I just
pretend not to know for just a little while, just one
day...)
Sorry, I might not be able to make it today

\nc<>Really!? There's nothing I can do... It's because you
specifically said it's impossible.

\nc<>I'll figure something out here. I don't know what happened,
but you should do your best too!

\nc<>(...I feel really guilty. But, this time...), (It was the
right choice, wasn't it...?)

\nc<>Oh, senpai. Are you still here? I heard that an incubus
appeared.

\nc<>B-But Reina said she has something important to talk
about...
\nc<>Hehe. So you were waiting for me? You're a good kid.
\nc<>But it's okay. That issue has already been resolved.
\nc<>So, senpai, please go quickly and help over there.

\nc<>Really? In that case... I'm sorry! I'll try to clean up as
quickly as possible and come back!
\nc<>Yes, I really... I've just stopped caring.
\nc<>Memory R2: Obtained a choice without regrets.
\nc<>I'm glad! I'll send you my location right away, meow!

\nc<>Sorry, Reina. I'll clean up as quickly as possible and come
back!
